  </section>

  <!-- ===================== GLOSSARY ===================== -->
  <section class="chapter" id="glossary">
    <span class="sec-num">Appendix B</span>
    <h2>Quick Glossary</h2>
    <div class="grid cols-2">
      <div class="card"><h4>Token</h4><p>The unit an LLM reads and generates — a word or word-fragment.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>Embedding</h4><p>A numeric vector representing the meaning of text; similar meanings sit close together.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>Context window</h4><p>The maximum amount of text a model can consider at once.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>Hallucination</h4><p>Fluent but factually wrong or unsupported model output.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>RAG</h4><p>Retrieval-Augmented Generation — grounding answers in retrieved documents.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>Vector database</h4><p>A store optimized for finding the nearest embeddings to a query.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>Agent</h4><p>An LLM that loops — planning, using tools, and observing results — to reach a goal.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>ReAct</h4><p>The Thought → Action → Observation loop at the heart of most agents.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>Tool / function calling</h4><p>Letting a model invoke external code, APIs, or data.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>MCP</h4><p>Model Context Protocol — an open standard for connecting agents to tools/data.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>Orchestration</h4><p>Coordinating multiple agents (and humans) toward a shared goal.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h4>Autonomy spectrum</h4><p>From fixed human-designed workflows to bounded self-directed agents.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  </main>
</div>

<footer>
  <div class="wrap">
    <p><strong>From LLMs to Agents</strong> — a developer's guide to Generative &amp; Agentic AI.</p>
    <p>Built for engineers beginning their journey. Every claim is cited to a primary, authoritative source listed in the References. Verify, don't trust — that is the engineer's discipline, and it is also exactly how we make AI trustworthy.</p>
  </div>
</footer>

<script>
  // Reading progress bar
  var bar = document.getElementById('progress');
  function update() {
    var h = document.documentElement;
    var scrolled = (h.scrollTop) / (h.scrollHeight - h.clientHeight);
    bar.style.width = (scrolled * 100) + '%';
  }
  document.addEventListener('scroll', update, { passive: true });
  update();

  // Highlight active TOC item
  var links = Array.prototype.slice.call(document.querySelectorAll('aside.toc a'));
  var sections = links.map(function(a){ return document.querySelector(a.getAttribute('href')); }).filter(Boolean);
  function spy() {
    var pos = window.scrollY + 120;
    var current = null;
    sections.forEach(function(sec){ if (sec.offsetTop <= pos) current = sec.id; });
    links.forEach(function(a){
      a.style.color = a.getAttribute('href') === '#' + current ? '#fff' : '';
      a.style.borderLeftColor = a.getAttribute('href') === '#' + current ? 'var(--brand)' : 'transparent';
      a.style.background = a.getAttribute('href') === '#' + current ? 'var(--panel)' : '';
    });
  }
  document.addEventListener('scroll', spy, { passive: true });
  spy();
</script>
